			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Steel slag is an industrial byproduct obtained from the steel manufacturing industry. It is produced in large quantities during steel-making operations that use electric arc furnaces. Steel slag can also be produced by smelting iron ore in a basic oxygen furnace. It is a by-product of steel making, produced during the separation of the molten steel from impurities in steel-making furnaces. The slag occurs as a molten liquid melt and is a complex solution of silicates and oxides that solidifies upon cooling.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">钢渣是钢铁制造业产生的一种工业副产品。使用电弧炉炼钢时会产生大量钢渣。在碱性氧气炉中冶炼铁矿石时也会产生钢渣。钢渣是炼钢的副产品，在炼钢炉中将钢水与杂质分离时产生。钢渣以液态熔体的形式出现，是硅酸盐和氧化物的复杂溶液，冷却后凝固。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Mixture of metal oxides and silicon dioxide</sumFormula>
